posts.body:
It doesn't bother me too much. I'm finding zeronet to be downright fascinating.
Whatever the seeding cache is called worries me a little though. A thread with around 500 replies chewed through the 10MB like nothing and no new posts appeared until I upped it, so that may be a problem.
What filetypes can we post anyway? Same as before or is there a new list?
Also, since I can now convey updates again, run BC on new versions. There was a rather insidious BC bug that was replacing .pornPrestigeDesc with .prestigeDesc that has been sorted out.
